# =============================================================================
# code-guda-gateway secrets + seed reference (UNTRACKED)
# =============================================================================
# Copy to:
#   Dev:  ~/.secrets/guda-gateway.env          (mode 0600)
#   Prod: operator secret store / one-shot seed shell on host (never commit)
#
# WHAT THE GATEWAY PROCESS READS AT RUNTIME (bootstrap only):
#   ADDR, DB_PATH, GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH, GUDA_ADMIN_COOKIE_SECURE
#   optional: GUDA_PROXY_DEBUG_ATTEMPTS
#
# EVERYTHING ELSE in this file is for:
#   - humans / agents daily ops (admin UI, MCP, curl)
#   - ./scripts/seed-provider-keys.sh (endpoint pairs + quota sidecars)
# The gateway does NOT load provider keys from env after seed.
#
# Source safely:
#   set -a; . ~/.secrets/guda-gateway.env; set +a
#   chmod 600 ~/.secrets/guda-gateway.env
# =============================================================================

# --- Bootstrap (process) -----------------------------------------------------
# Dev (persistent macOS):
ADDR=127.0.0.1:8080
DB_PATH=$HOME/.local/share/guda-gateway/gateway.db
GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH=$HOME/.local/share/guda-gateway/master.key
GUDA_ADMIN_COOKIE_SECURE=false

# Prod (example — do not mix DB and master key across combos):
# ADDR=127.0.0.1:8080
# DB_PATH=/var/lib/code-guda-gateway/gateway.db
# GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH=/etc/code-guda-gateway/master.key
# GUDA_ADMIN_COOKIE_SECURE=true

# --- Daily auth (MUST live in this file for daily use; not console-only) ----
# Admin UI login (hash is in SQLite; raw token here for you):
#   guda-gateway-admin --db "$DB_PATH" --master-key "$GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH" \
#     token init --save-env ~/.secrets/guda-gateway.env
#   # or: token rotate --save-env ~/.secrets/guda-gateway.env
GUDA_ADMIN_TOKEN=gat_REPLACE_ME

# Public gateway / MCP key (hash in SQLite; raw here for clients):
#   guda-gateway-admin --db "$DB_PATH" --master-key "$GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH" \
#     gateway-key create --name daily
# Paste printed gsk_… below after create.
GUDA_API_KEY=gsk_REPLACE_ME
GUDA_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# Prod public base (example):
# GUDA_BASE_URL=https://search.karldigi.dev

# =============================================================================
# Canonical production topology (endpoint pairs + quota sidecars)
# Names are identifiers only — NOT primary/backup roles.
# =============================================================================
#
# | name         | provider  | inference (upstream)              | quota mode              | quota target              |
# |--------------|-----------|-----------------------------------|-------------------------|---------------------------|
# | grok-1       | grok      | https://new.karldigi.dev/v1       | separate_credentials    | https://grok.karldigi.dev |
# | tavily-1     | tavily    | https://api.tavily.com            | endpoint_credentials    | same as inference         |
# | tavily-2     | tavily    | https://api.tavily.com            | endpoint_credentials    | same as inference         |
# | tavily-3     | tavily    | https://api.tavily.com            | endpoint_credentials    | same as inference         |
# | firecrawl-1  | firecrawl | https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2      | endpoint_credentials    | same as inference         |
#
# Grok: New API = inference token; Grok2API admin host = quota (admin key).
# Tavily/Firecrawl: official upstream; quota reuses same URL+key.
# =============================================================================

# --- Grok-1: New API inference + Grok2API admin quota ------------------------
GROK_1_NAME=grok-1
GROK_1_BASE_URL=https://new.karldigi.dev/v1
GROK_1_API_KEY=sk-REPLACE_ME_INFERENCE_TOKEN
GROK_1_QUOTA_MODE=separate_credentials
GROK_1_QUOTA_FLOW=grok2api_admin
GROK_1_QUOTA_BASE_URL=https://grok.karldigi.dev
# Grok2API admin key (app.app_key) — separate from inference token
GROK_1_QUOTA_KEY=REPLACE_ME_GROK2API_ADMIN_KEY

# Legacy aliases (seed script accepts these if GROK_1_* unset):
# GROK_API_KEY=...                    # same as GROK_1_API_KEY
# GROK_BASE_URL=https://new.karldigi.dev/v1
# grok2api_admin_base_url=https://grok.karldigi.dev
# grok2api_admin_key=...              # same as GROK_1_QUOTA_KEY
# grok_quota_mode=separate_credentials  # informational only; seed uses per-row set-quota

# --- Tavily 1–3: official API + shared endpoint credentials for quota --------
TAVILY_BASE_URL=https://api.tavily.com
# Preferred multi-key seed form (comma-separated → tavily-1, tavily-2, tavily-3):
TAVILY_API_KEYS=tvly-REPLACE_1,tvly-REPLACE_2,tvly-REPLACE_3
# Or explicit:
# TAVILY_1_API_KEY=tvly-REPLACE_1
# TAVILY_2_API_KEY=tvly-REPLACE_2
# TAVILY_3_API_KEY=tvly-REPLACE_3
# Quota: always endpoint_credentials / tavily_usage (default; seed enforces)

# --- Firecrawl-1: official API + shared endpoint credentials for quota -------
FIRECRAWL_1_NAME=firecrawl-1
FIRECRAWL_BASE_URL=https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2
FIRECRAWL_1_API_KEY=fc-REPLACE_ME
# Legacy alias: FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...
# Quota: always endpoint_credentials / firecrawl_credit_usage (default; seed enforces)

# =============================================================================
# Seed / migrate (prod, Coolify, or fresh host) — one coverage path
# =============================================================================
# Preferred (all steps, idempotent):
#   set -a; . /path/to/this.env; set +a
#   export DB_PATH GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH
#   ./scripts/seed-instance.sh [/path/to/guda-gateway-admin]
#
# That runs: db migrate → admin token → gateway-key → seed-provider-keys.sh
# Full matrix: scripts/templates/seed-flow.md
#
# Coolify (optional): after gateway is healthy,
#   docker exec -e … <container> seed-instance
#   or docker-compose.coolify-seed.yml --profile seed run --rm seed
#   or GUDA_SEED_ON_START=1 on the gateway service (heavier).
#
# Manual equivalent (same coverage):
# 1) Install binaries + bootstrap.env (no secrets) via install script.
# 2) Ensure DB_PATH + GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH pair exist (do not mix combos).
# 3) Migrate:
#      guda-gateway-admin --db "$DB_PATH" --master-key "$GUDA_MASTER_KEY_PATH" db migrate
# 4) Admin token + gateway key; always --save-env this file:
#      guda-gateway-admin … token init --save-env /path/to/this.env
#      # Coolify: token sync-env when GUDA_ADMIN_TOKEN is magic password
#      guda-gateway-admin … gateway-key create --name daily
#      # copy gsk_ into GUDA_API_KEY above
# 5) Seed endpoint pairs + quota:
#      ./scripts/seed-provider-keys.sh /path/to/guda-gateway-admin
# 6) Verify (safe metadata only):
#      guda-gateway-admin … provider-endpoint list
#      # grok-1: QUOTA_MODE=separate_credentials QUOTA_CONFIGURED=true …
#
# Existing rows: seed is idempotent on (provider, name).
# =============================================================================
